</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[188,1398,1386,1483]" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">
<bibRefCitation author="Bates H. W." box="[189,352,1386,1412]" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" pagination="153 - 224" refId="ref11396" refString="Bates H. W. 1881 a. Longicornia. In: Godman F. D. &amp; Salvin O. (eds) Biologia Centrali-Americana Insecta, Coleoptera Vol. 5: 153 - 224. Taylor &amp; Francis, London. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 730" type="journal article" year="1881">Bates (1881a)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[475,598,1386,1411]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Arixiuna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varians">
<emphasis box="[475,598,1386,1411]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">H. varians</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a series of males and females from 
<collectingCountry box="[1120,1210,1386,1412]" name="Mexico" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1264,1394,1386,1412]" name="Guatemala" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
, and reported on the elytral color (translated from Latin): “Elytra entirely fulvous, or posteriorly black and fulvous anteriorly, or with the humerus fulvous [remaining surface black].”
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[188,1399,1521,1689]" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">
<bibRefCitation author="Martins U. R. &amp; Galileo M. H. M." box="[189,496,1521,1548]" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" pagination="121 - 128" refId="ref13306" refString="Martins U. R. &amp; Galileo M. H. M. 1992. Generos de Hemilophini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae) relacionados com Hemilophus A. - Serville, 1835. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia 36 (1): 121 - 128." type="journal article" year="1992">Martins &amp; Galileo (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, erected 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1992" box="[603,705,1522,1548]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Arixiuna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[603,705,1522,1548]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Arixiuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and separated it from 
<taxonomicName authority="Audinet-Serville, 1835" authorityName="Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1835" box="[981,1399,1521,1548]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hemilophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[981,1123,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Hemilophus</emphasis>
Audinet-Serville, 1835
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of whitish pubescence on sides of the elytra (present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1835" box="[996,1138,1557,1583]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hemilophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[996,1138,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Hemilophus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and from 
<taxonomicName authority="Martins &amp; Galileo, 1992" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cuicirama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1271,1396,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Cuicirama</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martins U. R. &amp; Galileo M. H. M." box="[189,477,1592,1618]" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" pagination="121 - 128" refId="ref13306" refString="Martins U. R. &amp; Galileo M. H. M. 1992. Generos de Hemilophini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae) relacionados com Hemilophus A. - Serville, 1835. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia 36 (1): 121 - 128." type="journal article" year="1992">Martins &amp; Galileo, 1992</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the non orthogonal humerus (orthogonal in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1992" box="[1031,1156,1592,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cuicirama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1031,1156,1592,1618]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Cuicirama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Martins U. R. &amp; Galileo M. H. M." pageId="15" pageNumber="52" pagination="121 - 128" refId="ref13306" refString="Martins U. R. &amp; Galileo M. H. M. 1992. Generos de Hemilophini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae) relacionados com Hemilophus A. - Serville, 1835. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia 36 (1): 121 - 128." type="journal article" year="1992">Martins &amp; Galileo 1992</bibRefCitation>
). Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Galileo M. H. M. &amp; Martins U. R." box="[361,682,1627,1654]" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" pagination="103 - 109" refId="ref12275" refString="Galileo M. H. M. &amp; Martins U. R. 2005. Contribuicao aos Hemilophini da Costa Rica (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia 45 (10): 103 - 109. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0031 - 10492005001000001" type="journal article" year="2005">Galileo &amp; Martins (2005)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2005" box="[823,999,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hemilocrinitus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[823,999,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Hemilocrinitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and separated it from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1992" box="[1296,1399,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Arixiuna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1296,1399,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Arixiuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
especially by the antennal tubercles close to each other (distant in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="1992" box="[965,1068,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Arixiuna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[965,1068,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Arixiuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[188,1399,1728,1930]" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">
<bibRefCitation author="Hovore F. T." box="[189,363,1728,1755]" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" pagination="363 - 378" refId="ref12568" refString="Hovore F. T. 2006. The Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of Guatemala. In: Cano E. (ed.) Biodiversidad de Guatemala. Vol. 1: 363 - 378. Universidad del Valle de Guatemala, Guatemala City." type="journal article" year="2006">Hovore (2006)</bibRefCitation>
reported the geographical distribution of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[854,1052,1728,1754]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Arixiuna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varians">
<emphasis box="[854,1052,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Arixiuna varians</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as “eMEX (VC), GUA-CR”, meaning that the geographical distribution of the species is from east 
<collectingCountry box="[1046,1136,1763,1789]" name="Mexico" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1154,1265,1763,1789]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
), and from 
<collectingCountry box="[189,316,1798,1824]" name="Guatemala" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[352,484,1798,1824]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Swift I. P. &amp; Bezark L. G. &amp; Nearns E. H. &amp; Solis A. &amp; Hovore F. T." box="[493,706,1798,1824]" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 68" refId="ref14049" refString="Swift I. P., Bezark L. G., Nearns E. H., Solis A. &amp; Hovore F. T. 2010. Checklist of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of Costa Rica. Insecta Mundi 0131: 1 - 68." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Swift 
<emphasis box="[563,621,1798,1824]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
reported that the species occurs from 
<collectingCountry box="[1149,1239,1798,1824]" name="Mexico" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1253,1361,1798,1824]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
) to 
<collectingCountry box="[188,317,1833,1859]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[333,433,1833,1860]" country="Costa Rica" name="Heredia" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Heredia</collectingRegion>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne M. A." box="[452,621,1833,1859]" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" refId="ref13482" refString="Monne M. A. 2021. Catalogue of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of the Neotropical region. Part II. Subfamily Lamiinae. Available from https: // cerambycids. com / default. asp? action = show _ catalog [accessed 2 Aug. 2021]." type="url" year="2021">Monné (2021)</bibRefCitation>
reported the species as present in 
<collectingCountry box="[1027,1117,1833,1859]" name="Mexico" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1132,1243,1833,1859]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[1263,1393,1833,1859]" name="Guatemala" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[238,369,1868,1895]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
. We think that the report by Monné is better because, although it is very probable that the species also occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[449,563,1904,1930]" name="Honduras" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Honduras</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[620,744,1904,1930]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
, there is no evidence.
</paragraph>
